    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ukiyo-e print style or school associated with the port city of Nagasaki after 1750. Nagasaki-e prints primarily depict Dutch and Chinese foreigners, their customs, and ships, and were probably intended as souvenirs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
